race.comment: SEE YA LATER BABY (1) had been threatening to break through and did so in style here last start, putting his rivals away with ease. He rises in weight but now that he's found winning form, he's well placed to keep the momentum going. PRICILLA'S CHOICE (4) is flying, having bolted in here two back before a strong chasing second at Murray Bridge. She's holding her form beautifully and should be right in the finish again. CHARLESFORT (5) produced another big run at Strathalbyn, charging late to just miss. He'll get back from the draw but a solid tempo will suit, and he'll be launching hard. SIR RANDOLPH (3) is knocking on the door and doesn't need to improve much to win this. He's cherry-ripe now, draws well, and gets his chance. MAGIC PRINCESS (12) mixes her form but her best efforts measure up. Worth including.
